<div id="Idea_3563"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaTitle">
<a href="/akira/dtd/3563-4049"><span id="IdeaTitle_3563">Require all documents be available&nbsp;</span></a>
</div>
<table width=@%">  <tr>    <td valign="top"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaSubTitle"><b><a href="http://opengov.ideascale.com/akira/pmd/6746-4049">farseer2002</a></b> <span class="IdeaScale_SecondaryText">4 days ago</span></div></td>    <td align="right" valign="top"></td>  </tr></table>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaContent">All too often the government produces immense detailed documents such as Environmental Impact Statements, Remedial Investigation/Feasibility Studies (etc...) and bases these on a long list of government/contractor documents that contain the actually supporting data.  The devil hides in those details. <br/><br/>For ANY federal document or report released to the public- ALL of the referenced documents must be made readily and reasonably available (at least in electronic format) to all comers over the internet (as well as for physical inspection at some locations) prior to the document being released.</div>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaFooter"><span style="border-right: 1px solid silver; margin:0 10px 0 0; padding: 0 5px 0 0; color: #666;"><a id="DiscussionTopic_3563" href="javascript:ajaxLink('DiscussionTopicComment_3563', '/akira/discussion.do?mode=comment&dbid=2236&topicID=3563')">Comments (0)</a></span><span id="DiscussionTopicTag_3563"><a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?discussionID=2236">Making Data More Accessible</a>,&nbsp;<a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?mode=tag&tag=references available">references available</a></span></div><div style="margin-top:3px;" id="DiscussionTopicComment_3563"></div>
